1
00:00:01,262 --> 00:00:10,034
Vipassana Guidelines Whatever the sitting posture, it should be comfortable and fulfil three conditions.

2
00:00:10,894 --> 00:00:18,384
An energised spine with its natural curvature, the rest of the body relaxed and the head poised on top.

3
00:00:18,403 --> 00:00:21,868
The hands are placed on the lap and the eyes are gently closed.

4
00:00:23,751 --> 00:00:29,277
Then the attention is fixed on the process of breathing, just the normal and natural breath.

5
00:00:30,170 --> 00:00:34,956
It is the sensations of the abdomen caused by breathing which are to be observed.

6
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:40,462
And a noting word is used to focus the thinking mind onto these sensations.

7
00:00:41,704 --> 00:00:45,268
As the abdomen rises, the word rising is repeated.

8
00:00:46,088 --> 00:00:47,811
As it falls, falling.

9
00:00:49,313 --> 00:00:56,481
Feeling the sensations of the abdomen as neutral and pleasant, the heart is calmed and the mind is stilled.

10
00:00:57,322 --> 00:01:01,712
then the beginning and end of each in-breath and out-breath are more clearly seen.

11
00:01:03,856 --> 00:01:16,545
When the attention becomes somewhat steady, let it experience whatever draws it within the field of awareness, sensations and feelings, moods and emotions, mental images and thoughts.

12
00:01:17,638 --> 00:01:27,373
Using a simple word to note and without any interference whatsoever, all these passing phenomena are to be intimately felt and carefully observed.

13
00:01:28,474 --> 00:01:39,512
Should the mind wander, let it be brought back gently but firmly to observe sensations at the abdomen in order to cultivate a sharp attentiveness.

14
00:01:41,703 --> 00:01:48,412
In this way, right awareness with intuitive intelligence, satipaṋña, becomes established.

15
00:01:50,715 --> 00:02:06,376
This bare attentiveness, simply watching all that arises and passes away, this choiceless awareness that does not control or manipulate, this impartial observation that does not judge or question,

16
00:02:07,218 --> 00:02:28,078
This intuitive introspection, fully experiencing each physical, emotional and mental event as it really is, leads to the realization that everything is impermanent and insubstantial and that to identify with or to become attached to anything whatsoever will bring dissatisfaction.

17
00:02:29,538 --> 00:02:33,883
These vipassana insights into the three characteristics of existence

18
00:02:34,217 --> 00:03:00,580
impermanence, unsatisfactoriness and not-self, anicca, dukkha, anatta, lead to the complete liberation from all suffering, the experience of the unborn, the unbecome, the undying, the uncreated, the unconditioned, true refuge, harbour and home, perfect happiness and contentment.

19
00:03:02,197 --> 00:03:05,950
Those who are mindful are in the presence of Nibbana.

20
00:03:07,938 --> 00:03:08,722
Sadhu.

21
00:03:10,026 --> 00:03:10,748
Sadhu.

22
00:03:11,973 --> 00:03:13,117
Sadhu.

